verbs.description: disfurnish (third-person singular simple present disfurnishes, present participle disfurnishing, simple past and past participle disfurnished)

entries.meaning: (transitive, archaic) To deprive of that with which anything is furnished (furniture, equipment, etc.); to strip or divest.
examples: I am a thing obscure, disfurnish'd ofAll merit, that can raise me higher.
